    <thetext>While trying to run MADNESS (https://github.com/m-a-d-n-e-s-s/madness/) I get the error message

$ mpirun -np 2 ../../../../objdir/src/apps/moldft/moldft h2o_9_lda.in 
!! Error: MPI_Init_thread did not provide requested functionality: THREAD_MULTIPLE (THREAD_SERIALIZED). 
!! Error: The MPI standard makes no guarantee about the correctness of a program in such circumstances. 
!! Error: Please reconfigure your MPI to provide the proper thread support. 

so it&apos;d be nice if OpenMPI were compiled with --enable-mpi-thread-multiple.</thetext>
